    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-01T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-01T12:00:00-05:00" n="807"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d807">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12683: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-01T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 1, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 1—12:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2765. Department’s 2276, June 24, 8 p.m.,<note n="20" xml:id="d807fn20">See
                        footnote 13, <ref target="#pg_749">p. 749</ref>.</note> was communicated
                    informally to the Foreign Office with the comments suggested and a letter has
                    been received from Sir Alexander Cadogan<note n="21" xml:id="d807fn21">British
                        Permanent Under Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs.</note> which
                    concludes with the following paragraph: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I am sure that our military authorities in the Middle East are already
                            taking all possible steps compatible with the pursuit of military
                            operations to minimize civilian sufferings, but the offer of the United
                            States Government is being brought to their attention.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
